# Project: plonky3-experiments

## Rust Toolchain
- The project is pinned to Rust 1.95.0 via `rust-toolchain.toml`
- Always verify the active toolchain with `rustup show` before coding
- Never use `stable`, `beta`, `nightly`, or an unpinned toolchain for this repo
- Treat `rust-toolchain.toml` as authoritative for compiler version and components
- If any required component is missing, stop and report the exact `rustup component add --toolchain 1.95.0 ...` command needed
- Run checks with the pinned toolchain and do not introduce code requiring a newer compiler

## Stack
- Rust (check Cargo.toml for exact crate versions)
- Plonky3 crates from crates.io


## Goals
- Experiment with field arithmetic over the Goldilocks field
- Prototype FRI-based polynomial commitments
- Build small circuits and verify proofs end-to-end

## Module Conventions
- One module per concept: `fields/`, `fri/`, `circuits/`
- Every public `fn` has a doc comment with a usage example
- Tests live alongside source in `#[cfg(test)]` modules
- Benchmarks in `benches/` using Criterion

## Increment Size
Keep each agent increment to ~100 lines as per git-workflow skill.
Split into separate branches if a feature spans more than ~300 lines.

## Toolchain policy
- Do not change `rust-toolchain.toml` or `Cargo.toml` Rust version unless explicitly asked
- Use the pinned Rust 1.95.0 toolchain for checks and tests